text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd: 
 Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany

 1.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 2.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 3.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 4.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 2.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 3.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 4.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 5.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 6.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.

 1.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 2.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 3.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 4.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 5.Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
 6.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

 5.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.

 2.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
 3.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 4.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 5.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 6.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
